    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-09T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-09T07:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/10–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-09T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 9, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 9—9:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8491. Comea 109. Through its acting representative on the European Advisory
                    Commission, Sobolev,<note n="1" xml:id="d171fn1">Arkady Aleksandrovich Sobolev,
                        Soviet Minister-Counselor in the United Kingdom.</note> the Soviet
                    Government has agreed to amend the draft protocol on zones of occupation in
                    Germany in accordance with the arrangement worked out at Quebec three weeks ago
                    between the United States and United Kingdom Governments. The text advanced by
                    the British delegation and amendments to incorporate these changes in the
                    protocol was forwarded in my 8137 [<hi rend="italic">8237</hi>], (September 29,
                    5 p.m., Comea 102). Department’s 8098 October 3, midnight, Eacom 33, reported
                    that the text of the delineation of the United States and United Kingdom zones
                    had not yet been approved by the Combined Chiefs of Staff. Lacking clearance on
                    these amendments, action in the EAC is at a standstill because the United States
                    delegation is not in a position to present its proposals for amendment <pb
                        facs="0366" n="352" xml:id="pg_352"/> and thus to complete the essential
                    tripartite agreement on zones of occupation. Gousev is temporarily absent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
